<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 23 at 9:18PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A LINE OF SHOWERS WILL AFFECT CASWELL...PITTSYLVANIA AND WESTERN
HALIFAX COUNTIES AND THE CITY OF DANVILLE...
At 917 PM EDT, radar indicated showers with heavy rains were located
along a line extending from near Pittsville to Hamer. Movement was
northeast at 25 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph are possible with these showers.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Altavista...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Hurt...
Chatham...
and Gretna.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these showers, and may
cause localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</description>
